        <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-12 content">
          <div class="anchor" id="getting-started"></div>
          <h1>Getting Started for Vue or React Developers</h1>
          <p>
            Using our components in your existing Vue application is very
            easy. All you need to do is to enable our components either
            through our npm package or simply use one of our CDN links.
          </p>
          <p> 
            If you would like to see our components in an existing Vue
            application we have created a demo Vue project which uses
            JJ-components below.
          </p>
          <h2 id="vue-demo">
            Vue Demo
          </h2>
          <a href="https://github.com/yiy142/jayjay-vue">https://github.com/yiy142/jayjay-vue</a>.
          <p>
            The main points to recognize is that in out demo Vue project we
            use our CDN. In <code>jayjay-vue/public/index.html</code> we
            include the CDN to the JJ-components we wanted to import. This
            enables the entire application to use our components which can be
            seen in <code>jayjay-vue/src/components/HelloWorld.vue</code>.
          </p>

          <h2 id="react-demo">
            React Demo
          </h2>
          <a href="https://github.com/rkeng/jj-react-demo">https://github.com/rkeng/jj-react-demo</a>.
          <p>
            The main points to recognize is that in out demo Vue project we
            use our CDN. In <code>jj-react-demo/public/index.html</code> we
            include the CDN to the JJ-components we wanted to import. This
            enables the entire application to use our components which can be
            seen in <code>jj-react-demo/src/App.js</code>.
          </p>
      </div>

